title: ComponentSource Announces 2022 Publisher and Product Award Winners
excerpt: Atlanta, GA (PRWEB) February 22, 2022 -- The world's largest marketplace for software components and development tools announces their latest global awards for 2022
summary: ComponentSource 2022 Publisher & Product Awards These awards are based on orders we received from our global customers. They represent a true global market snap-shot for commercial software components and development tools in 2021 Atlanta, GA (PRWEB) February 22, 2022 ComponentSource®, the world's largest marketplace and community for reusable software components and development tools today announced their latest Awards for 2022 for both leading publishers and their individual products. The awards have been given to the Top 100 Bestselling Publishers and the Top 100 Bestselling Products, based on the total sales dollar value of orders placed by customers during the year (2021) through ComponentSource worldwide.

Companies from Japan constitute more than a third of the list as the shape and pace of global innovation continues to shift east

LONDON, Feb. 23, 2022 /PRNewswire/ -- Clarivate Plc (NYSE:CLVT), a global leader in providing trusted information and insights to accelerate the pace of innovation, today released the Top 100 Global Innovators™ 2022 list. Drawing on Clarivate™ data, the annual list identifies the organizations that demonstrate consistent, above-the-bar innovation excellence and which sit at the very top of the global innovation ecosystem.

title: Watch: Westminster home explosion caught on camera
author: Dara Bitler
excerpt: The Westminster Fire Department says a home exploded early Tuesday morning. The explosion was captured on a Ring camera.
summary: by: Dara Bitler Posted: Feb 22, 2022 / 07:11 AM MST / Updated: Feb 22, 2022 / 07:16 AM MST WESTMINSTER, Colo. (KDVR) — The Westminster Fire Department says a home exploded early Tuesday morning. The explosion was captured on a Ring camera. You can watch the video in the player above. Blaine Leishman shared the video with FOX31 and Channel 2. A few seconds into the video, you can hear a loud boom and then a see debris flying across the screen. Then a few seconds later, smoke is spotted in the distance.
